```Based on the search results, I'll now compile the answer about Apple Singapore's return policies for custom optical inserts, volume purchases, and price protection policiesBased on my research of Apple's Singapore Consumer Store policies, custom third-party prescription optical inserts cannot be returned once ordered, as they are personalized items [1]. For volume purchases defined as an aggregate of more than four items, Apple requires customers to contact Business Team for specific return arrangements, as standard consumer return policies may not apply [2].

Regarding return location, time limits, and restocking fees: standard Apple products typically have a 14-day return window when returned to an Apple Store in Singapore, with no restocking fees if items are in original condition [3]. However, custom items like prescription optical inserts are non-returnable due to their personalized nature [1].

For price protection, Apple Singapore offers refunds if the price of a product is reduced within 14 calendar days of purchase [4]. Customers must contact Apple Support or visit an Apple Store with their receipt to request the price adjustment. This policy applies to products purchased directly from Apple and excludes limited-time promotions, special financing offers, and prices from third-party retailers [4]. Educational pricing and corporate purchases may also have different terms for price protection eligibility [4].

